Certainly! Here's a simple HTML/JS code snippet that will transform the mock-up into a functional website with two real jokes. This code will create a webpage with a title, a joke section, and a button to reveal the second joke.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Joke Website</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
            margin: 0;
        }
        .container {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        .joke-container {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
        }
        .joke {
            margin: 10px;
        }
        .button {
            background-color: #007bff;
            color: white;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        .button:hover {
            background-color: #0056b3;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="joke-container">
            <div class="joke">
                <p>Joke 1:</p>
                <p>Why did the tomato turn red?</p>
                <p>Because it saw the salad dressing!</p>
            </div>
            <div class="joke">
                <p>Joke 2:</p>
                <p>Why did the scarecrow win an award?</p>
                <p>Because he was outstanding in his field!</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div>
            <button onclick="revealJoke()">Reveal Joke 2</button>
        </div>
    </div>
    <script>
        function revealJoke() {
            const joke2 = document.querySelector('.joke p').innerHTML;
            document.querySelector('.joke p').innerHTML = joke2;
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

This code will create a webpage with a title, two joke sections, and a button to reveal the second joke. When the button is clicked, the second joke will be displayed in the first joke section. The joke sections are styled to be centered and the button is styled with a gradient background color.
